{
  "text": "According to this study, CEOs support the vision of corporate communicators \"becoming facilitators of two-way and multi-directional conversations\" (Arthur P. Society, 2007 p. 17) . They ought to change their role enactments. Instead of mainly speaking out to publics, communicators can be experts who investigate the dynamics of public opinion building, interests of key stakeholders and multipliers, as well as emerging networks and interactions those groups. [CITATION_1] analyzed the perceptions of eight CEOs and 24 senior managers in New Zealand.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "144639324"
  },
